Itaque eam . . . inventa sunt: note the irony in this passage3 these are Cicero’s words, adopting Caesar's recommendation and carrying it out to its final issue to show how great severity it really involves. Bear in mind that Cicero himself favors the death penalty proposed by Silanus; hence he here artfully seeks to prove that imprisonment for life is after all the severer penalty of the two.
